# threeSecondRule3D (Godot 4.7)

First-person 3D driving game: get to work (**3 miles**) while practicing the **3-second following rule**. Main scene: `res://scenes/main.tscn`.

## Architecture

| Script | Role |
|--------|------|
| `scripts/game_manager.gd` | Win/lose, HUD updates, following-time display, restart on Enter |
| `scripts/player_vehicle.gd` | Speed, lane snap, movement along +Z, traffic-aware coasting catch-up, crash signal |
| `scripts/traffic_manager.gd` | Spawn/despawn NPC traffic, spacing, player collision, `get_following_seconds()`, lead-car fallback |
| `scripts/traffic_car.gd` | NPC bus movement, loads/fits `assets/vw_bus.glb`, exposes `get_rear_z()` / `get_front_z()` |
| `scripts/road_manager.gd` | Recycled road segments |
| `scripts/dashboard_hud.gd` | In-cockpit SubViewport readouts (Digital-7 TTF, plain labels) |
| `scripts/vehicle_audio.gd` | Engine loop + optional brake/crash; stops engine on crash |

Traffic scene: `scenes/traffic_car.tscn` (root + script only; model spawned at runtime).

Engine audio node: `World/Player/VehicleAudio/EngineLoop` (`AudioStreamPlayer` in `main.tscn`, stream `res://assets/audio/cruising.wav`).

## Controls (`project.godot` input actions)

- **Up / Down** — accelerate / decelerate (hold; ramps over time)
- **Space** — brake (hold; strong ramp)
- **A / D or Left / Right arrows** — snap to adjacent lane (not continuous strafe)

## Lane & coordinate conventions

- Road forward is **+Z**. Lanes at `x = -1.85` (left) and `x = 1.85` (right).
- Camera is X-flipped, so `lane_left` action sets `LANE_RIGHT_X` and `lane_right` sets `LANE_LEFT_X` in `player_vehicle.gd` — **do not swap back** without checking in-game feel.
- Lane changes use `move_toward` to `target_lane_x` on key press (`is_action_just_pressed`).

## Traffic & 3D assets

- NPC vehicle model: **`res://assets/vw_bus.glb`**. Prefer **glTF/GLB** for new vehicle assets.
- `traffic_car.gd` loads the GLB at runtime, scales to `TARGET_LENGTH` (4.5 m), centers on road, caches bumper offsets from mesh AABB.
- Default `model_rotation_degrees` is `Vector3.ZERO`.
- `@export model_extra_scale` for manual tuning in the inspector.

### Sketchfab / vw_bus.glb caveats

- Export has **messy bounds** (e.g. huge internal dimensions, generic `Object_*` names). `_estimate_vehicle_length()` rejects outlier axes (`MAX_MESH_AXIS`, 8× ratio rule).
- **Do not use fixed `CAR_LENGTH` offsets** for gap math — use `_rear_z_offset` / `_front_z_offset` from fitted mesh bounds.
- **Wheel spin was attempted and removed.** Do **not** re-add rim rotation unless a new model has dedicated wheel nodes/bones.

### Following time (3-second rule)

- Formula: **`gap / player_speed`** (time headway at the driver's speed). **Not** closing speed / speed difference.
- Gap is **bumper to bumper**: `lead.get_rear_z() - player.get_front_z()` (`get_front_z()` = player `z + 1.8`).
- HUD shows **`--`** when no car in lane (`get_following_seconds()` ≥ 90).

### Traffic spacing & catch-up (6-second ceiling)

Game keeps the player in the pack; the driver owns spacing **at or below 6 seconds**.

| Constant | Value | Role |
|----------|-------|------|
| `MAX_FOLLOW_SECONDS` | **6.0** | Hard ceiling — game intervenes above this |
| `MIN_CAR_GAP` | 10 m | NPC car-to-car spacing |
| `LANE_SPAWN_SPACING` | 22 m | Spawn spacing per lane |
| `SPAWN_MIN_AHEAD` | 60 m | Initial spawn distance ahead |

**Player (`player_vehicle.gd`)** — when coasting (no accel/decel/brake): if follow time **> 6 s**, ramp speed toward the lead car's mph (`AUTO_CATCHUP_MPH`); if below **40 mph** with no traffic chase, floor at `CRUISE_MIN_MPH`.

**Traffic (`traffic_manager.gd`)** — fallback if gap **> 6 s** at current player speed: teleport/spawn lead car to **6 s** (`CATCHUP_COOLDOWN_SEC = 4`). Requires `@export traffic_path` on Player → TrafficManager.

## Dashboard HUD (`dashboard_hud.gd`)

Plain **Digital-7 TTF** (`res://digits/digital-7.regular.ttf`) — **no** LED sheets, outlines, glow, or `FontDigitDisplay`/`LedDisplay`.

| Readout | Value format | Captions |
|---------|--------------|----------|
| Miles to destination | `%.1f` | Miles to / Destination |
| MPH | integer | MPH |
| Following time | `%.1f` or `--` | Following / Time |

- Value font **72 px**; caption font **16 px** (`COLOR_CAPTION`).
- Following colors: green ≥ 3 s, yellow ≥ 1.5 s, red below.

## Audio (`vehicle_audio.gd` + `main.tscn`)

- Engine: **`res://assets/audio/cruising.wav`** on scene node `EngineLoop` (`autoplay`, `volume_db ≈ 10`).
- **Do not `duplicate()` `AudioStreamWAV`** for the engine — breaks playback after ~0.5 s in Godot 4.7. Assign/import stream directly; use `finished` → `play()` if loop import is insufficient.
- Import: `edit/normalize=false`, `compress/mode=0` (PCM), `edit/loop_mode=1` preferred.
- No pitch or speed-based volume yet (user may add later). Brake/crash paths optional (`brake.ogg`, `crash.ogg`).

## GDScript conventions (this project)

- Use **explicit `float` types** when inference fails, e.g. `var world_z: float = _lane_spawn_z[lane_x]`.
- Defer model fitting: `call_deferred("_fit_model_to_road", model)` after adding the GLB child.
- Keep traffic logic in `traffic_manager.gd`; lane constants must stay in sync across `player_vehicle`, `traffic_manager`, and `traffic_car`.
- `MAX_FOLLOW_SECONDS` is duplicated in `player_vehicle.gd` and `traffic_manager.gd` — keep both in sync.

## Editor / tooling

- **godot_ai** MCP plugin enabled (`addons/godot_ai/`). Requires **`uv`** on the system (`brew install uv` on macOS). Do **not** use the dock **Install uv** button if it hangs — install in Terminal instead.
- **Cursor MCP**: `~/.cursor/mcp.json` needs a `godot-ai` entry (Configure in Godot AI dock, or `"url": "http://127.0.0.1:8000/mcp"`). Godot must be open with server connected; refresh MCP in Cursor after Mac sleep.
- Large assets: headless import — `Godot --headless --import --path <project>`.
- Do not commit secrets. Avoid editing `addons/godot_ai/` unless fixing the plugin itself.

## When changing vehicles

1. Drop GLB in `assets/`, let Godot import, update `BUS_MODEL_PATH` if filename changes.
2. Verify orientation via `model_rotation_degrees` (likely 0 or 180 on Y).
3. Re-check HUD follow time and collision gaps after any model swap — visual position must match `_cache_extent_offsets()`.
4. For animated wheels later: require separate wheel nodes with pivots at hub centers, or a rigged model.
